ld aggro in this place? We had an enchanter, shaman, wizard and cleric tank with warriors as the toned down rangers. <br><br>Just to give you an idea on the aggro ping-pong:  <br><br>Ench 30% aggro<br>Shaman 25% aggro<br>Cleric 10% aggro<br>Wizard 10% aggro<br>Warrior 1 &amp; 2 - share 25% aggro.<br><br>This is an approximate. <br><br>Just to point out these mobs are BLUE, which means to a 60 warrior they SHOULD be subject to our taunt - but I felt like I was playing DaoC and not EQ.  <br><br>To top all this @#%$ off, the mobs AOE slowed.  50% of the time they got me, which resulted in less aggro, which reduces dmg output etc.  Finally I lost my patience and dumped ALL my MR gear on my and dropped all of my AC.  MR = 189...did they still slow me ? course they frigging did.  <br><br>So am I right in saying a level 59 enchanter PC who has tashed me(drops to around 139MR) and empties all their mana on TRYING to get ANYTHING to stick cant do it, yet a blue mob(i.e.less than 59) who HASNT tashed me can get through 189MR ? That is total Bullshit. <br><br>I tell you this, if I was the other 4 non-melee in the group looking for tanks and there was 1 paladin, 1 rogue, 2 warriors LFG at zone .... Even IF the warriors were 60 and the paladin / rogue were level 55.  I would take the paladin and rogue.  <br><br>I have seen a paladin tank this zone without any sweat.  Even if they are slowed, that dont stop em from chain stunning the mobs to pieces to keep aggro. <br><br>Oh and to top it off amphibious(sp?) creatures 100% resistant to my FIRE based procs - I dont think so.<br><br>BOO! CT<br><br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/uraluvinssteele.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raluvin Ssteele</A> at: 3/15/02 4:53:45 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/uvaldayana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valdayana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ruler of Quellious</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(3/15/02 6:21:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=220.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Raluvin actually FLAMES!!!!</span><hr size=1> *Poke* As someone who's pretty much been in Cazic Thule nightly since the change.. it's a different zone, and still likely bugged in some ways, but that makes it a unique challenge.  While the Manastone doesn't work, and things can be mesmerized as per Kunark and later rules, taunt and charm are strictly old world in Cazic.. there is none.  In the old world you were never allowed to taunt or charm level 51+ monsters, and hey, everything in the new Cazic is level 51+!  The zone is being patched as I write this though, so it might be being addressed.. if it doesn't get changed, then yes, hybrids will remain the best tanks at least for holding agro.  It's not really that bad to have one zone where they're preferable to warriors..<br><br>As for the AE slow, it checks against Disease Resist, not Magic Resist.  Some of the lizards proc it randomly, others will proc poison rains or AE heals, depending on the class of the lizard.  It can also be cured with a Counteract Disease casting, and heals you for 35000 HP over its duration, 700 a tick.  I am not making that up.  And yes, that is a bug and will be fixed next patch.<br><br>Valdayana D'Varr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/bquelliousquaterstherebirth.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=saltamontes>Saltamontes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 197<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(3/15/02 8:19:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=220.topic&index=2>Reply